### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

For example, this code:
```
<button>
  <!-- prettier-ignore -->
  <ng-container
    *ngIf="condition; else other"
    i18n="@@text"
  >
    ICU: {count, plural, =1 {item} other {items}}
  </ng-container>
  <ng-template #other>Bar</ng-template>
</button>
```

will be converted to this:
```
<button>
  <!-- prettier-ignore -->
  @if (condition) {
    <ng-container i18n="@@text">
      ICU: {count, plural, =1 {item} other {items}}
    </ng-container>
  } else {
    Bar
  }
</button>
```

However, as the comment has meaning (to ignore the next block from formatting with prettier), this now causes a change in behaviour, as the inner ng-container is no longer ignored from formatting. 

Ideally, the comment would be printed inside the condition, like this:
```
<button>
  @if (condition) {
    <!-- prettier-ignore -->
    <ng-container i18n="@@text">
      ICU: {count, plural, =1 {item} other {items}}
    </ng-container>
  } else {
    Bar
  }
</button>
```

The same problem occurs for eslint ignore comments like this `<!-- eslint-disable-next-line @angular-eslint/template/rule -->` inside templates, they are now no longer printed before the line they are meant to disable and no longer have the desired effect.

